# Inventory / Marketplace MVP

Internal inventory is the **source of truth**, integrated with marketplaces (Shopee/Tokopedia
now). **Adapter-first with STUBS** so the whole pipeline runs without real provider APIs.
Per-user scoped (internal-first, multi-tenant-ready). Roadmap + locked decisions:
`docs/roadmap/inventory-mvp.md`.

## Modules & domains
- **catalog** — Product / ProductVariant (master). Server service owns Prisma (no repository).
  Every product has ≥1 variant; SKU `@@unique([userId, sku])`. Variant carries `cost`/`weight`,
  `lowStockThreshold`/`alertEnabled`, and reorder planning `leadTimeDays?`/`minOrderQty?` (0 in the
  UI = unset → null). Variants are editable: `PATCH /products/:id/variants/:variantId` →
  `updateVariant` (create/add-variant forms stay short; advanced planning is set later via Edit).
  Stock changes go through the inventory service, NEVER by writing inventory tables from catalog.
- **inventory** — `Inventory` (fast-read cache: available/reserved/damaged/incoming) +
  **`StockLedger` (append-only = the real source of truth)**. Every mutation = 1 ledger row + 1
  Inventory update in ONE tx. `adjustStock` (manual, never negative); `applyOrderDecrementTx(tx,…)`
  (order sale, MAY go negative). Surfaces: `getDashboard` (KPIs); `listStockOverview` (now also the
  last movement before→after + `lastAdjustedAt`, via a nested `take:1` ledger include); **reorder
  report** (`inventory-reorder.service` — recency-weighted/EWMA velocity → days-of-cover → suggested
  qty, honours per-variant lead time/MOQ; bucketed ledger sums per sub-window); **stock activity
  log** (`inventory-activity.service` — filter reason/source/direction/date + paginate + CSV export).
  Demand reasons for velocity are centralised in `SALES_LEDGER_REASONS` (ORDER_RESERVE+RELEASE, NOT
  SHIP — avoids double-count). Pure `utils/stock-math.ts` + `utils/reorder-math.ts` are unit-tested.
- **marketplace** — connections (`MarketplaceConnection`; now also `lastOrdersPulledAt`) +
  `MarketplaceProduct` (listing snapshot) + `MarketplaceProductMapping` (listing↔variant). Mapping
  is **1:1 on the listing** (`marketplaceProductId @unique`) but ONE variant MAY map to many
  listings — cross-channel sync is by design, do NOT force 1:1. Import via STUB adapter; auto-map by
  NORMALIZED sku (`utils/sku-match.ts`, NOT edit-distance — `…-M` ≠ `…-L`); non-exact →
  `NEEDS_REVIEW` + sync stays off (per-listing sync is a **Switch**, disabled while NEEDS_REVIEW).
  `mapByExternalRef` upserts a listing (creating its snapshot if never imported) + its mapping.
- **orders** — **multi-store pull** `pullFromConnections(connectionIds?)` (default every active
  store; STUB adapter) → resolve items via mapping → PAID, not-yet-applied order decrements stock +
  stamps `Order.inventoryAppliedAt` (idempotency) → propagate to OTHER channels. Per-store **30s
  cooldown** keyed on `lastOrdersPulledAt` (skipped, not errored = anti-abuse). `resolveOrderItem`
  maps an unmapped item from the order page (via `mapByExternalRef`) then decrements stock for just
  the newly-resolved items (idempotent). Endpoints: `POST /api/v1/orders/pull`,
  `/orders/:id/resolve-item`. Pull lives on the **Orders** page (removed from marketplace detail).

## Outbound sync engine (worker-side) — `packages/queue/src/marketplace-sync/`
SoT change → `enqueuePropagateInventoryStock` (web, best-effort, only if `syncEnabled` mappings
exist) → `propagate-inventory-stock` job (fan-out, idempotent per ledger event) →
`sync-marketplace-stock` job → `executeStockSync` (per-provider rate-limit, push LATEST
available via the provider adapter; `Dev` stub simulates success, `Unwired` stub rejects) →
marks `MarketplaceSyncJob` + mapping `lastSyncStatus` + listing snapshot. Retryable failures
throw so BullMQ retries.

## Cross-module composition (respect boundary §3)
- catalog→inventory ONLY via the inventory service (no cross-table writes). orders→inventory via
  `applyOrderDecrementTx`. A module may import another module's HOOKS/types but NOT its
  components — cross-module UI composition lives at the APP layer (e.g.
  `app/(dashboard)/dashboard/products/[id]/product-detail-view.tsx` wires catalog `ProductDetail`
  + inventory `AdjustStockDialog`). The variant picker reuses inventory `useStockOverviewQuery`.

## Gotchas (learned the hard way)
- **BullMQ custom jobId CANNOT contain `:`** → job-id builders use `-` (DB idempotency keys keep `:`).
- A real provider adapter needs the **DECRYPTED token** → lift marketplace token-crypto into a
  shared `@olshop/*` package (the engine passes the encrypted token; stubs ignore it).
- A running dev server (`tsx watch server.ts`) holds the Prisma query-engine DLL on Windows →
  `prisma generate` fails `EPERM`. Stop it before generate/migrate; restart after. BUT an
  index-only / no-client-change migration can run with `prisma migrate dev --skip-generate`
  WITHOUT stopping the dev server (only `generate` overwrites the locked DLL).
- `next build` intermittently fails `Failed to collect page data for /<page>` while node procs
  run (a `.next` file-lock flake) — just re-run; not a code error.
- `server-only` services can't be imported into a worker-context `tsx` script without
  `node --conditions=react-server` + the web tsconfig.

